      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Vlad Stamate</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:VladStamate.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/74/VladStamate.jpg/300px-VladStamate.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/7/74/VladStamate.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:VladStamate.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Vlad Stamate <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Vlad Stamate</b>,<br />\nan American computer scientist, software and game developer with Romanian roots. \nHe studied at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politehnica_University_of_Bucharest\">Politehnica University of Bucharest</a> \nand graduated in CS with a B.Sc. degree in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphic_design\">graphic design</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richmond,_The_American_International_University_in_London\">Richmond, The American International University in London</a> in 2001. \nActually affiliated with <a href=\"/index.php?title=Apple&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Apple (page does not exist)\">Apple</a>, Vlad Stamate worked in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research_and_development\">R&amp;D</a> department of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sony_Computer_Entertainment\">Sony Computer Entertainment America</a>, leading the <a href=\"/GPU\" title=\"GPU\">GPU</a> performance analysis software team for the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PlayStation_3\">Playstation 3</a> console, \nand as an engineer for <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imagination_Technologies\">Imagination Technologies</a> taking part in developing <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenGL\">OpenGL</a> <a href=\"/Linux\" title=\"Linux\">Linux</a> drivers <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe has published various articles of the advanced <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rendering_(computer_graphics)\">rendering</a> techniques book project <i>ShaderX</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. \nand further started chess programming in 2006 on a program called <b>ps3chess</b>, followed by <b>ps3chess2</b>, <b>fastthink</b> and in January 2009, <a href=\"/Plisk\" title=\"Plisk\">Plisk</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>.\nAs collector of old and antique computers since 2012, Vlad Stamate features the <b>Digilogue Museum</b> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>, \nalong with the <b>Digilogue Collection</b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YouTube\">YouTube</a> channel <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publication\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publication</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2009\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2009</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publication\">Selected Publication</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vlad_Stamate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publication\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Reduction of lighting calculations using Spherical Harmonics</i>. in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.shaderx3.com/Tables%20of%20Content.htm\">ShaderX3 - Advanced Rendering Techniques</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i>Real-time damage deformation methods</i>. in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.shaderx4.com/TOC.html\">ShaderX4 - Advanced Rendering Techniques</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>Real Time Photon Mapping Approximation on the GPU</i>. in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://shaderx6.com/TOC.html\">ShaderX6 - Advanced Rendering Techniques</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vlad_Stamate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2009\">2009</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vlad_Stamate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2009\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=28523\">Incremental Zobrist - slow?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 20, 2009 &#160;» <a href=\"/Incremental_Updates\" title=\"Incremental Updates\">Incremental Updates</a>, <a href=\"/Zobrist_Hashing\" title=\"Zobrist Hashing\">Zobrist Hashing</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29077\">Killer moves (ply or depth?)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 22, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Killer_Heuristic\" title=\"Killer Heuristic\">Killer Heuristic</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29366\">Single legal move - what to do?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 12, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/One_Reply_Extensions\" title=\"One Reply Extensions\">One Reply Extensions</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29577\">Generating \"through\" attacks with rotated bitboard</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 28, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Rotated_Bitboards\" title=\"Rotated Bitboards\">Rotated Bitboards</a>, <a href=\"/X-ray_Attacks_(Bitboards)\" title=\"X-ray Attacks (Bitboards)\">X-ray Attacks (Bitboards)</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29658\">Finding mate fast</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 04, 2009</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vlad_Stamate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=32254\">XBoard and epd tournament</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 31, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Chess_Engine_Communication_Protocol\" title=\"Chess Engine Communication Protocol\">Chess Engine Communication Protocol</a>, <a href=\"/Engine_Testing\" title=\"Engine Testing\">Engine Testing</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=32424\">Standpat and check</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 06, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Quiescence_Search#StandPat\" title=\"Quiescence Search\">Standing Pat</a>, <a href=\"/Check\" title=\"Check\">Check</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=32897\">TT hit/miss rates</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 25, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Transposition_Table\" title=\"Transposition Table\">Transposition Table</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=33084\">Zero window TT entry</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 05, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Null_Window\" title=\"Null Window\">Null Window</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=33685\">Long game vs short game testing</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 08, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Engine_Testing\" title=\"Engine Testing\">Engine Testing</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=34051\">Ponder console input move problem</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 28, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Pondering\" title=\"Pondering\">Pondering</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=34795\">Opening book formats and UIs</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 08, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Opening_Book\" title=\"Opening Book\">Opening Book</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=35428\">Abusing a chess program</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 14, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=35471\">WCRCC 2010 - Plisk games</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 17, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/WCRCC_2010\" title=\"WCRCC 2010\">WCRCC 2010</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=35699\">New rating system research</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 05, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=41058\">2011 ACCA Pan American CCC - Plisk games</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 12, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/ACCA_2011\" title=\"ACCA 2011\">ACCA 2011</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Vlad_Stamate&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/vlad-stamate-427955/\">Vlad Stamate | LinkedIn</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/pliskchess/\">PliskChess</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://sites.google.com/site/digiloguemuseum/\">DigiLogue Museum</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC7HbC_nq8t1S9l7qGYL0mTA\">Digilogue Collection - YouTube</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rwj1bFJqw_s\">Computer History: Vintage Computer Collection Part 1</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Vlad Stamate</a>, June 18, 2018, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YouTube\">YouTube</a> Video</li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <div class='embedvideo ev_inline ev_top autoResize' style=' width: 646px;'><div class='embedvideowrap' style='width: 640px;'><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/Rwj1bFJqw_s?\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true